    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a lemma showing that for any finite set <code>A : Set T</code>, there is function <code>f : Fin A.card -&gt; T</code> such that <code>Finset.image f Finset.univ = A</code></p>",
        "id": 502803145,
        "sender_full_name": "Frederick Pu",
        "timestamp": 1740875328
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>another variation is that if <code>[LinearOrder T]</code> then for any finite set <code>A : Set T</code> there is a function <code>f : Fin A.card -&gt; T</code> such that <code>StrictMono f</code> and <code>Finset.image f Finset.univ = A</code></p>",
        "id": 502803375,
        "sender_full_name": "Frederick Pu",
        "timestamp": 1740875564
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Finset.orderIsoOfFin#doc\">docs#Finset.orderIsoOfFin</a> helpful?</p>",
        "id": 502808120,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1740879826
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ig, but i think a lemma of the specific form im talking about could be useful</p>",
        "id": 502813505,
        "sender_full_name": "Frederick Pu",
        "timestamp": 1740884498
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>would it be possible to open an issue for this</p>",
